{"title":"Host Deep Dive Usage","type":"markdown","aggs":[],"params":{"fontSize":12,"openLinksInNewTab":false,"markdown":"# Dashboard Usage
Use this handy little guide to make the most of this dashboard. 
Any questions or recommendations can be sent to Lt Goldstein (901 CPT).

### Login History
Just a chronological list of who has logged in. It does not currently show failed logins. Use the [Logon Activity](https://kibana.kit05-837/app/dashboards#/view/9e43e320-2a55-11ee-a289-c1af0fc179f8) dashboard for that.

### Suspicious Parent
This table shows processes that were spawned by unusual parents.
Currently the list of unusual parents is limited to:
* cmd
* powershell
* wscript
* cscript

### SYSTEM Network Connections
This panel is targeted towards Sysmon Event ID 3 and further filtered to the SYSTEM account. It will show the process establishing the connection, the target IP, and target port. 

### Registry Modifications
This panel is targeted towards Sysmon Event ID 12, 13, and 14. It will return the process, registry key, value being modified, and the user account that made the modification.

### Unique Commands Executed
This panel focuses on process execution. It groups unique commands executed by user account. Because it's a unique count, the count associated is irrelevant. A 1 does not mean it was only ran once. "}}
